### PART 1 — Enhanced LangFuse Visualization Dashboard

#### Page: `/platform/observability`

Build a dashboard that consumes LangFuse's API and renders the following:

**Trace Explorer Panel**
- Filterable, paginated table of traces (by date range, user, session, model, tags, 
  status: success/error)
- Expandable row → Trace Detail Drawer showing:
  - Full span tree (parent/child hierarchy) rendered as a collapsible tree with 
    duration bars (Gantt-style mini-chart using Recharts or a custom div-based renderer)
  - Token usage breakdown per span (prompt tokens, completion tokens, cost estimate)
  - Input/output display with syntax highlighting (use `shiki` or `highlight.js`)
  - Metadata, tags, scores displayed as badges

**Metrics Cards Row** (top of page)
- Total traces (today / 7d / 30d toggle)
- Average latency (P50, P95, P99)
- Total token usage + estimated cost
- Error rate %
- All cards animate on load and support drill-down click

**Latency & Usage Charts**
- Line chart: Latency over time (P50/P95 overlay)
- Bar chart: Token usage by model (grouped)
- Area chart: Trace volume over time
- All charts use Recharts, are responsive, and support tooltip with full data

**Scores & Evaluation Panel**
- Table of LangFuse scores (human feedback, LLM-as-judge results)
- Score distribution histogram
- Filter by trace, scorer, score name

**Sessions View**
- Group traces by session ID
- Show session timeline, total cost, user journey reconstruction

**Datasets & Experiments Panel**
- List all LangFuse datasets with item counts and last-updated
- Click into a dataset → view items, expected outputs, linked runs
- Experiment comparison table: side-by-side runs with score comparisons, latency delta, 
  cost delta — highlight winning run in green

