### PART 2 — Prompt Management & GitLab MR Merge Trigger

#### Page: `/platform/prompts`

**Prompt Catalog View**
- List all LangFuse prompts with: name, labels, active version, last updated, tags
- Filter by label (production / staging / feature/*), search by name
- Click → Prompt Detail page

**Prompt Detail Page**
- Version history timeline (vertical stepper component)
- Side-by-side diff view between any two versions (use `diff` npm package + custom 
  renderer with red/green line highlighting)
- Prompt variables extracted and displayed as a schema table
- "Promote to Production" manual button (role-gated — admin only)
- Commit history panel (GitLab MR linked if metadata present)

**Prompt Merge Engine (Core Feature)**

Architecture:

  [GitLab Webhook] 
       ↓
  POST /api/webhooks/gitlab
       ↓
  Validate X-Gitlab-Token secret
       ↓
  Filter: event = "merge_request", state = "merged", target_branch = "main"
       ↓
  Extract branch name → derive LangFuse prompt name via naming convention
       ↓
  Call LangFuse API: get latest version of feature prompt
       ↓
  Call LangFuse API: create new version of production prompt with feature content
       ↓
  Apply labels: remove "feature/*", add "production"
       ↓
  Log merge event to platform audit log
       ↓
  Post comment back to GitLab MR with merge result summary

Implement:
- `app/api/webhooks/gitlab/route.ts` — webhook receiver with HMAC signature validation
- `lib/langfuse.ts` — typed LangFuse API client (wrapping `langfuse` SDK and raw API 
  calls for prompt management)
- `lib/gitlab.ts` — GitLab API client for posting MR comments
- `lib/prompt-merge.ts` — core merge logic: convention parsing, conflict detection, 
  merge execution, rollback on failure
- Naming convention parser: `{prefix}/{branch-slug}--{prompt-name}` → extracts 
  `prompt-name` as the production target
- Conflict detection: if production prompt was updated after the feature branch prompt 
  was created, flag a conflict and post a warning comment to the MR instead of 
  auto-merging; create a conflict record in the platform DB for manual resolution

**Merge History & Audit Log Panel** (on `/platform/prompts` page)
- Table of all merge events: timestamp, MR link, branch, prompt affected, status 
  (success / conflict / failed), triggered by
- Click → Merge Detail Drawer showing full diff of what was merged, GitLab MR metadata, 
  and rollback button (admin only)

**Conflict Resolution UI**
- List of unresolved prompt conflicts
- Side-by-side editor (production version vs feature version) with merge controls:  
  "Accept Feature", "Accept Production", "Merge Manually" (opens an editable textarea 
  prepopulated with feature version)
- On resolve → calls LangFuse API to create new production version + marks conflict 
  resolved in audit log

